<br>
First off, technically a level 60 ogre SK is a noticably better puller than a level 60 monk, death peace is a near instant effect spell, and the recast time is 1/5 of the monk FD regen time. A decent high level SK can have 1250+ unbuffed ac. We have non damaging spells (so that the mob can't summon) that can be used to pull from afar  (Although Holgresh Beads are a damn sight better). Against smaller targets we can snare a named and feign, the common mobs reset to spawn points where the named has barely moved and can be reaggroed sans common mobs, effectively solo pulling a named from a room full of junk. <br>
<br>
Now that FD works, Sks can immediately gain and lose aggro as they see fit. If a MT ever loses aggro, and the mob aggroes on one of the &quot;softer&quot; classes, a SK can instantly capture aggro with the AC drain line/darkness/(heh and now our skill taunt ain't half bad either), then lose it before he gets dead allowing a cleric to heal him without getting any aggro at all as the SK has lost it from feigning.<br>
<br>
Problem with the SK class is that only a couple old school vets are around anymore. Of the 4 Sks that came over from Sol Ro, I am the only one left(Eviscerator retired, Larazel went DaoC, and Necor is on Ant Bayle with Darkwind), and I am even gettin bored with it. Hehe hell there are only 1 or 2 ogre SKs left on our server and they by far make the best Sks on just about every server. (Fore is from back when leveling an ogre or troll took twice as long as a human due to xp table differences and I didn't know there was 1000 hp diff at level 60, heh I didn't even know there was gonna be a level 60)<br>
<br>
Damage wise we are hurting as far as raids go, but now that our taps are resisted a whole lot less against ultra spawns we can chain tap 300 300 300 300 300 300 300 and not only keep ourselves healed up, but by timing it right we can steal a kill with a well timed disc HT making it look like we do uber damage and can be cool too.<br>
<br>
Sks are the most complicated tank class by far, we have too many options for many of the casual Sk players to handle at once. I could see why some people don't like them, but I can guarantee, I have twice as much fun playing a SK, than you do playing any other class.<br>
<br>
BTW, rangers might not look like a usefull class at first, but try this, turn on others hits in your chat filter, they may not look cool, but they bring the hurt(a 650pt DD proccing dagger indeed) and they have tons of toys (IE SoW buffs snare and bow crits for billions of points of damage :P). I mean hey, at least they aren't paladins, would suck to be known as a portable one use instant CH. <br>
LOL and someone said paladins can outtaunt a SK, the day a paladin outtaunts me, is the day I turn in my spurs.<br>
